article.description: Andrea Riley scored 23 points and Oklahoma State (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) routed Eastern Kentucky 90-35 on Monday night.
article.headline: Riley scores 23 points as Cowgirls outman Colonels
article.linkText: Riley pace No. 23 Oklahoma State in rout
article.story:
STILLWATER, Okla. -- Andrea Riley scored 23 points and Oklahoma State (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) routed Eastern Kentucky 90-35 on Monday night.

Riley, the Big 12 Conference's leading scorer (22.2 ppg), also had seven assists, five rebounds and four steals for the Cowgirls, who won their sixth straight.

Taylor Hardeman scored 17, Tegan Cunningham had 16 and Shaunte Smith had 12 for Oklahoma State (8-2).

The Cowgirls turned up the defensive pressure midway through the first half, when Eastern Kentucky turned the ball over 15 times.

After a basket by Kayla Drake made it 15-11, the Cowgirls outscored Eastern Kentucky 34-10 to take a 49-21 lead at the break. Oklahoma State widened its advantage with a 20-2 run in the second half, when the Lady Colonels (3-6) scored just 14 points.

Drake led Eastern Kentucky with 11 points and eight rebounds.
